        In the equation Ax=b, the input vector x and the output vector b are both in \R^2.
        First we multiply A by a vector to see what it does:
        A\vec{x y} = \mat{1 0; 0 1}\vec{x y} = \vec{x y}.
        Multiplication by A does not change the input vector at all: it is the identity transformation which does nothing.

