        First we multiply A by a vector to see what it does:
        A\vec{x y} = \mat{1 1; 0 1}\vec{x y} = \vec{x+y y}.
        Multiplication by A adds the y-coordinate to the x-coordinate; this is called a shear in the x-direction.

